<h2>Project Overview</h2>
<p>
This project consists of the design and implementation of a modern
Data Warehouse architecture using SQL Server. The objective was to
structure operational data to enable efficient analytical queries
and support business intelligence reporting.
</p>

<h2>Architecture</h2>
<p>
The solution follows a multi-layer architecture commonly used in
modern data platforms:
</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Bronze Layer:</strong> Raw data ingestion from operational systems.</li>
<li><strong>Silver Layer:</strong> Data cleansing, normalization and preparation.</li>
<li><strong>Gold Layer:</strong> Business-ready data models optimized for analytics.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Data Modeling</h2>
<p>
A dimensional model using a <strong>Star Schema</strong> was implemented to
optimize analytical queries and facilitate reporting.
Fact tables store transactional information while dimension tables
provide descriptive business context.
</p>

